# HabitIQ Project Roadmap

This roadmap outlines the development journey of **HabitIQ**, an AI-powered habit insight and prediction tool built with Python.  
The project is divided into clear phases to ensure structured development and continuous improvement.

---

## 1: Planning & Setup
**Goals:** Establish the foundation and environment for development.  
**Tasks:**
- [x] Define project scope and objectives  
- [x] Create GitHub repository and folder structure  
- [x] Draft README.md and requirements.txt  
- [x] Install core libraries: `pandas`, `numpy` 
- [x] Set up version control and initial commits  
  

---

## 2: Core Functionality Development
**Goals:** Build the basic system for tracking and storing user habits.  
**Tasks:**
- [x] Develop user input system  
- [x] Create habit logging for name, time, mood, and energy  
- [x] Implement data storage using  
- [x] Add basic validation and data management functions  
  

---

## 3: Data Analysis & Pattern Recognition
**Goals:** Analyze user data and identify meaningful trends.  
**Tasks:**
- [ ] Process logged data with Pandas and NumPy  
- [ ] Detect correlations between time, mood, and success rate  
- [ ] Generate summary reports and trend insights  


---

## 4: Predictive Modeling & Insights
**Goals:** Enable AI-powered habit prediction and personalized insights.  
**Tasks:**
- [ ] Train machine learning models (Decision Tree / Random Forest)  
- [ ] Predict likelihood of habit completion  
- [ ] Provide personalized habit recommendations  


---

## 5: Data Visualization
**Goals:** Visualize data for clear habit tracking and progress review.  
**Tasks:**
- [ ] Design visual charts and habit streak displays  
- [ ] Use Matplotlib or Plotly for trend visualization  
- [ ] Integrate visuals into the GUI/dashboard  
 

---

## 6: Testing & Refinement
**Goals:** Improve performance, usability, and reliability.  
**Tasks:**
- [ ] Debug core modules and fix logic issues  
- [ ] Conduct user testing and collect feedback  
- [ ] Optimize model accuracy and interface responsiveness  
 

---

## 7: Documentation & Final Release
**Goals:** Prepare the final project for submission or release.  
**Tasks:**
- [ ] Write detailed documentation and setup guide  
- [ ] Update README.md, CHANGELOG, and LICENSE  
- [ ] Add screenshots or demo GIFs  
- [ ] Package and upload final release version  
 

---

## Future Enhancements
- Google Calendar integration for smart scheduling  
- Gamification features (points, badges, streak rewards)  
- Mobile version using Kivy  
- Cloud data sync for multi-device use  

